Show HN: Create a managed hosting service for Open Source software
text:
I recently launched Go Open Cloud – a platform where open source software teams can easily create a hosted version of their software. It leverages Docker images to create a fully managed cloud instance and includes support for premium packages users can purchase using PayPal.

The best part is that users can try out the software with a single click. No need to install anything. Check out our website for more details: https://www.go-open.cloud.

To see how this service looks when it's being used, take a look at: https://nococloud.dev/.

I'd love to hear your thoughts and feedback. Let me know what you think!
